## 7. Retrieval logic with pgvector

`app/retrieval.py`:

```python
from typing import List, Tuple
from sqlalchemy import text as sql_text
from .db import SessionLocal
from .embeddings import embed_text


def semantic_search(query: str, k: int = 8) -> List[Tuple[str, str]]:
    """
    Returns list of (kind, text) for top-k chunks.
    """
    session = SessionLocal()
    try:
        vec = embed_text(query)
        # cosine distance example; adjust for your pgvector setup
        sql = sql_text(
            """
            SELECT kind, text
            FROM doc_chunks
            ORDER BY embedding <-> (:embedding)::vector
            LIMIT :k;
            """
        )
        rows = session.execute(sql, {"embedding": vec, "k": k}).all()
        return [(r.kind, r.text) for r in rows]
    finally:
        session.close()
```



You can extend this with filters (e.g., prioritize rules, D4, etc.) by adding `WHERE` clauses on `kind`, `domain`, `hemisphere`. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/attachments/472397461/6a7af292-0594-469c-9efd-679614782eb3/STOICHEION_AXIOM_PAYLOAD.md)

